H0.text: The river Danube flows into which sea. Black Sea

H1.text: The river Danube flows into which sea. Adriatic Sea

H2.text: The river Danube flows into which sea. Caspian Sea

H3.text: The river Danube flows into which sea. Euxine

A4.text: It flows through Central and Southeastern Europe, from the Black Forest of Germany south through the Danube Delta in Romania into the Black Sea.

A5.text: The Danube then flows southeast for about 2,730 km (1,700 mi), passing through four capital cities (Vienna, Bratislava, Budapest, and Belgrade) before emptying into the Black Sea via the Danube Delta in Romania and Ukraine.
